summary:
With more than 12 years of experience working as a banking professional, participating in global banking transformation programs, Strong Knowledge of financial products in corporate and retail industry. During my different operational roles, I have developed client management skills demonstrated in quick and efficient problem solving and turn-around time. Aware and observant of risks inherent in transaction, relationships, and information handling. Highly self-motivated and action oriented professional blending business administration and banking experience with the passion of human development. Furthermore, delivered several high-profile projects to achieve the change priorities required by the organization through implementing lean Six Sigma and change management best practices, while ensuring relevant regulatory requirements and policies are met. Driven to achieve results through determination and commitment. I am flexible, team player, conscientious and trustworthy and enthusiastic about my work.	
 Supported by my bachelor’s degree in Economics and Accounting, in addition to my master’s in international business. I consider myself a professional, who have the adequate knowledge and experience to propose and customize the adequate strategies and solutions.
